## ARITHMETIC & OPERATORS

- - - /  %          // add, sub, mul, div, modulo
      i / j                  // integer division — truncates toward zero
      i % j                  // remainder (same sign as dividend in C)
      -i                     // negate

// Integer division examples
7 / 2   → 3            // truncates
7 % 2   → 1
-7 / 2  → -3           // truncates toward zero (C99+)
-7 % 2  → -1

// Float division
(float)i / j           // cast to avoid integer division
7.0f / 2               // → 3.5

// Increment / decrement
i++;  ++i;
i–;  –i;

// Compound assignment
i += 5;  i -= 3;  i *= 2;  i /= 4;  i %= 3;

